FBIS4-58399 "drnes086_n_94008" FBIS-NES-94-086 Daily Report 4 May 1994 LEBANON Amal-Hizballah Tension Prevails in South Amal-Hizballah Tension Prevails in South NC0405080894 Kafr Killa Voice of the South in Arabic 0700 GMT 4 May 94 NC0405080894 Kafr Killa Voice of the South Arabic BFN [Text] Our correspondent reports that tension is prevailing between the Amal Movement and Hizballah activists in 'Aytit and neighboring villages against a background of incidents involving the two parties in the past two days. The correspondent adds that the incidents took place after Hizballah elements provoked Amal Movement elements in the village. Tension also prevails in Qa'qa'iyat al-Jisr and other villages in the al-Nabatiyah district after Amal Movement elements accused Hizballah elements of killing Amal official Ni'mah Haydar about two weeks ago.
